"Blanco J.M., Mendía F., Peña F.","Comparative analysis of CO2 and SO2 emissions between combined and conventional cycles with natural gas and fuel oil consumption over the Spanish thermal power plants",2006,"Fuel","85","9",,"1280","1285",,,10.1016/j.fuel.2005.12.001,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-32544442321&partnerID=40&md5=d9a6f6bdea3efab63bdaabc7ae5ba22c","Depto. Máquinas y Motores Térmicos, Universidad del País Vasco, E.H.U., Alameda de Urquijo s/n, 48013 Bilbao, Spain","Blanco, J.M., Depto. Máquinas y Motores Térmicos, Universidad del País Vasco, E.H.U., Alameda de Urquijo s/n, 48013 Bilbao, Spain; Mendía, F., Depto. Máquinas y Motores Térmicos, Universidad del País Vasco, E.H.U., Alameda de Urquijo s/n, 48013 Bilbao, Spain; Peña, F., Depto. Máquinas y Motores Térmicos, Universidad del País Vasco, E.H.U., Alameda de Urquijo s/n, 48013 Bilbao, Spain","The concern over 'global warming' and 'acid rain', stands out the possibility of re-converting fuel-oil boilers into natural gas, because SO 2 emissions would be almost annulled but also because it would mean a great decreasing of 'carbon' in the fuel matrix, reducing also CO2 emissions. Another important fact is the progressive substitution of conventional power plant schemes for combined cycles, due mainly to their higher efficiency. In this paper, a comparison (in terms of emissions) was carried out between both cycles for natural gas and fuel-oil consumption over a representative Spanish thermal power plant. Finally, a comparison with experimental values has been performed. © 2006 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.","Combined cycles; Emissions; Fuel","Acid rain; Fuel oils; Global warming; Natural gas; Sulfur dioxide; Combined cycles; Emissions; Thermal power plant; Carbon dioxide",,,,,,"Garea, A., Herrera, J.L., Marques, J.A., Irabien, A., (2001) Chem Eng Sci, 56, pp. 1387-1393; Chisholm, P.N., Rochelle, G.T., (1999) Ind Eng Chem Res, 38, pp. 4068-4080; Weinell, C.E., Jensen, P.I., Dam-Johansen, K., Livbjerg, H., (1992) Ind Eng Chem Res, 31, pp. 164-171; Mastsers, K., (1991) Spray Drying Handbook, , 5th ed Wiley New York; Bird, R.B., Stewart, W.E., Lightfoot, E.N., (1960) Transport Phenomena, , Wiley New York; Perry, R.H., Chilton, C.H., (1973) Chemical Engineer's Handbook, , 5th ed McGraw-Hill New York; Izquierdo, J.F., Fite, C., Cunill, F., Iborra, M., Tejero, J., (2000) J Hazard Mater, 76, pp. 113-123; Matsukata, M., Takeda, K., Miyatani, T., (1996) Chem Eng Sci, 51 (11), pp. 2529-2534; Stein, J., Kind, M., Schlunder, E.U., (2002) Chem Eng J, 86, pp. 17-23; Kiil, S., Nygaard, H., Johnsson, J.E., (2002) Chem Eng Sci, 57, pp. 347-354; McCabe, W.L., Smith, J.C., Harriott, P., (1988) Unit Operations of Chemical Engineering, , 4th ed McGraw-Hill New York; McCabe, W.L., Smith, J.C., Harriott, P., (1988) Unit Operations of Chemical Engineering, , 4th ed McGraw-Hill New York; Uchida, S., Tsuchiya, K., (1984) Ind Eng Chem Process des Dev, 23 (2), pp. 300-307; Huang, W.J., Test methods for air pollutants (1998) ROC EPA NIEA Method, , [A412.70A]; Himmelblau, D.M., (1962) Basic Principles and Calculations in Chemical Engineering, , Prentice-Hall New Jersey; Van, G.J., Sonntag, R.E., (1985) Fundamentals of Classical Thermodynamics SI Version, , 2nd ed Wiley New York","Blanco, J.M.; Depto. Máquinas y Motores Térmicos, Universidad del País Vasco, E.H.U., Alameda de Urquijo s/n, 48013 Bilbao, Spain; email: nmpblilj@bi.ehu.es",,,,,,,,00162361,,FUELA,,"English","Fuel",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-32544442321
